WPK Anniversary Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- Celebration meetings were held in Russia, Mongolia, India and Romania from Sept. 23 to 30 with the approach of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Chairman Oleg Shenin of the Communist Party of the Soviet Union, made an opening address at the meeting held in Moscow under the sponsorship of the party, Secretary Vladimir Beryodin made a report and the chairman of the Central Executive Committee of the International Union of Officers of the Soviet Union, the president of the Russian People's Academy of Sciences and others speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Oleg Shenin said that the WPK founded by President  Kim Il Sung is the guiding force of the Korean people and the six decades of the WPK reflect the glorious revolutionary history of the President and leader Kim Jong Il. 
 As they have the WPK, headquarters of the revolution, the Korean people have come to shape their destiny by themselves and the WPK has come to steer the new era of independence as the party with steadfast independence, he added.
 The reporter and speakers said that Kim Il Sung founded the WPK and developed it into a powerful guiding force of the revolution and performed the undying exploits which will shine in the century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They noted that Kim Jong Il modeled the whole party on the Juche idea and thus the Juche idea serves as the guiding idea of the party and weapon of socialist construction in Korea and thanks to his wise guidance of the party the DPRK has turned into an invincible socialist bulwark on which any enemy dare not pounce.
 Referring to the fact that Kim Jong Il has developed and enriched the Juche idea with his unique Songun politics, they stressed that the history of the WPK has been successfully carried forward by him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the meeting a performance was given by Russian artistes to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president of the Federation of Peace and Friendship Organizations of Mongolia, in his speech said that the DPRK has become a dignified and developed country thanks to the perfect unity of the leader, party, army and people of Korea and their steadfast belief that the master of one's destiny is himself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 V. K. Chopra, chairman of the Indian Intellectuals' Society for the Study of the Juche Idea, said in his speech that Kim Jong Il has performed immortal exploits in his leadership over the whole work of the party and the state, working at the Central Committee of the WPK from 40 odd years ago and he is infinitely trusted by all the Korean people for his outstanding leadership art and popular traits.
 Congratulatory messages and letters to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings held in Russia, Mongolia and India.

KCNA Assails Japan for Peddling "Abduction Issue" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- The ultra-right conservative forces of Japan are still peddling shamelessly the "abduction issue' which had already found a solution.
 This is evidenced by a statement released by the "Society of Abductees' Families" and the "Association for Rescuing Abductees," both made up of the above-said forces.
 The statement blustered that "unless the issue of the repatriation of abductees is settled at the dialogue with north Korea, there is no other option but to apply economic sanctions against it to express the will of the state to bring back all the abductees".
 This meant the Japanese ultra-right conservative forces' total denial of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration, a clear indication that they have no political will to normalize the relations with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They made much ado about "false remains" and "accurate examination" only to become a laughing stock of the world. Yet, they do not bother to resort to such political rowdyism aimed at further deteriorating the bilateral ties, again stoking the atmosphere of confrontation under the present situation. Why? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is prompted by their political and strategic aim to drive their government to sustaining its hostile policy towards the DPRK come what may.
 As six decades have already passed since Japan's defeat, the issue of its settlement of past crimes has become the focus of the international community's attention. The international community including Asian countries strongly urge the Japanese government to immediately come out for this settlement, unanimously denouncing Japan's imprudent attempt to evade its commitment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's settlement of its crimes perpetrated against the Korean people in the past is an issue that should be solved without fail for the normalization of the relations between the DPRK and Japan as was stressed by the Pyongyang declaration.
 It is as clear as daylight that the issue of Japan's settlement of its past should be discussed in case an inter-governmental contact takes place between the two countries for the normalization of the bilateral relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said ultra-right conservative forces again trumpeted about the worn-out "abduction issue," thus admitting themselves that they are playing the role as a shock brigade in egging the government on to evade the settlement of the past wrongs. Lurking behind this move is a sinister intention to improve their public image and, at the same time, to create at home and abroad a climate favorable for their hostile policy towards the DPRK and their policy of veering to the Right. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is not allowed to behave as it pleases as far as the issue of its settlement of its past is concerned. It is not the issue that allows Japan to cover it up. 
 Japan kidnapped and forcibly drafted at least 8.4 million Koreans in the last century and even now it is persisting in luring and abducting operations in the DPRK-China border area. However, it is loudmouthed about the issue which had already been settled, while keeping mum about their cases of abduction committed by it for more than a century. This is absolutely unpardonable. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is ridiculous of those ultra-right conservative forces to try to apply economic sanctions against the DPRK under pretext of the "abduction issue". 
 The Korean people have strong faith as they have built independent national economy and accomplished everything despite the enemy's vicious and persistent sanctions that have lasted for several decades. The DPRK is strong in its faith as it has made progress on its own. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That is why the DPRK and its people remain unfazed even in face of Japan's threat and provocation such as "sanctions" or "stop to the humanitarian aid."
 The Japanese government must be well aware of this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Should the Japanese government cling to the hostile policy towards the DPRK, dancing to the tune of the ultra-right forces, it will only result in vitiating the atmosphere of the progress to normalize the relations between the DPRK and Japan and pushing the present confrontation to the point of explosion. The DPRK never says empty words.

GNP of S. Korea Accused of Hamstringing Development of Inter-Korean Relations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- Some days ago the "National Assembly" of south Korea decided to reorganize the "special committee for the development of the south-north relations" tasked to ensure "transparency" and "prior consultation" while "reviewing" the inter-Korean relations.
 Commenting on this, papers here Tuesday observe: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "The special committee" was initiated by the Grand National Party of south Korea which has played only a negative role after poking its nose into the issue of inter-Korean relations and the reunification issue. The committee is, therefore, nothing but a product of the anti-reunification plot of the ultra-right conservative forces of the GNP to arrest the progress of the national history and bring the present inter-Korean ties back to the old era of confrontation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst of Rodong Sinmun notes: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The NA's "review" of the inter-Korean cooperation which has been under way according to the fellow countrymen's will for reconciliation and reunification could not produce anything positive because the NA has undergone  turns and twists due to the intrigues of the GNP. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
In actuality, the NA has not yet expressed any support to the June 15 joint declaration though it is five years since it was adopted to be hailed at home and abroad.
 The NA should no longer play into the hands of such anti-reunification forces as the GNP as they have been keen to deter the inter-Korean relations from improving and incite anti-north confrontation by reorganizing the "special committee". Explicitly speaking, there is no justification whatsoever to create such "special committee." 
  The reality goes to prove that neither the aspiration of the south Korean people for independence, democracy and reunification nor the development of the inter-Korean relations can come true as long as the anti-reunification conservative forces including the GNP are allowed to remain in the NA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the NA is to make a genuine contribution to the development of the inter-Korean relations, it should not talk about "transparency" in undertakings for cooperation but see through the anti-reunification attempt of the GNP, contain and reject this traitorous group and take a practical action to scrap the "National Security Law" extremely harmful to the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A commentary of Minju Joson warns that the NA's decision to reorganize the "special committee" is little short of digging its own grave.

U.S. Urged to Build Confidence in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- It is quite different from the U.S. commitments that the U.S. bellicose elements have ceaselessly improved and completed the plan to invade the DPRK and accordingly deployed its huge forces of aggression in and around south Korea, leading the situation of the Korean Peninsula to the brink of war, Rodong Sinmun says in a signed commentary today. 
If the U.S. has no intention to invade the DPRK and wants the peace of the Korean Peninsula, it should not work out a new war scenario nor deploy ultra-modern forces in and around south Korea, Rodong Sinmun points out, and goes on:
 The U.S. is stepping up its preparations for another war behind the scene of dialogue, while amending its military strategy towards the orientation of reliance on the latest weapons under the pretext of coping with a possible military conflict with north Korea.
 Preserving peace in the Korean Peninsula is a prerequisite to ensuring the peace and security of Northeast Asia and the rest of Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hastening U.S. establishment of new military strategy relying on latest weapon is an open challenge to the peace of the Korean Peninsula and the peace of Asia and the rest of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is paying a lip service to the peace of the Korean Peninsula. But the U.S. invariable ulterior intention to stifle the DPRK and dominate the whole of Korea is evoking the vigilance and apprehension of the Korean people and the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. continued reinforcement of forces of aggression in and around south Korea is to ignite another Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The strike of the DPRK is powerful and invincible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has already declared that it would not need even a nuke if DPRK-U.S. relations are normalized, confidence built and the DPRK feels no longer to fear the U.S. nuclear threat. It is high time that the U.S. got rid of the old Korea policy of the era of Cold War and took a decisive measure for building confidence in the DPRK. 
 The essence of the settlement of the DPRK-U.S. relations is to build confidence and this is not an exception to the settlement of the nuclear issue.

WPK Exploits Will Be Everlasting, Says Rodong Sinmun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today carries an editorial article under the title "The exploits of the Workers' Party of Korea that has won victory after victory with Songun will be everlasting".
 The WPK is a revolutionary party of Juche type which was founded and strengthened with the anti-Japanese tradition of Songun as its firm root, the article says, and goes on:
 The WPK is a glorious party which originated in the Songun revolution. The cause of party building was pioneered in the unique way of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The pioneering of the anti-Japanese revolution was the origin of the cause of Juche-oriented party building in our country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Party is unshakable in any storm and stress as it took root in the rigorous and bloody long journey of the Songun revolution and has steadily developed with the principle of arms as its nutritious element. Herein lies the unique character and feature of the Party as a Juche-oriented revolutionary party and its everlasting vitality. 
 The Party is a revolutionary party of a new type guided by the Juche idea and the Songun idea based on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Party was founded and has developed with the firm organizational and ideological foundation laid in the arduous struggle of the anti-Japanese revolution and the revolutionaries of arms as its hard core. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of party building is that of party building of Songun type which was pioneered and consolidated firm with Songun. For the Party Juche is Songun and Songun is Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Party is an ever-victorious party that has performed great undying exploits in the history of socialist politics under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Party is a great guide which has built Korean style socialism centering on the popular masses and led it to a continued prosperity. From the very day of its foundation the Party set up a power representing the will and interests of the people with the army as its mainstay, prepared the political force enough to undertake the tasks of great social revolution and the material guarantee for the establishment of the socialist system in reliance on military power from scratch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The superior and unique Korean-style socialism where the popular masses emerge as the master of everything and everything serves them is the tower of socialist success which was erected with Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the firm will of the Party to rapidly develop national defence,  economy and culture with great Songun politics, bring the DPRK up to the position of the strongest in the world and put forward the Korean people as the most dignified and happy people in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK is an ever victorious party which has firmly defended the sovereignty of the country and the dignity of the nation with Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the strong arms the Party has provided a phase of final victory, taking the initiative even at the time of extreme trials and difficulties while closely watching the internal and external situation. The history of the Party's leadership over the "arduous march" has been embroidered with the traces of the Songun politics which has helped to cement its powerful self-defensive military muscle in every way in the worst adversity. 
 The WPK is a glorious party that has laid the foundation for eternal victory of our revolution under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the most valuable asset for victory of the Songun revolution that leader Kim Jong Il has systematized and completed the Songun idea and politics as a great strategic programme for the accomplishment of the cause of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the Songun politics of the Party the people's army has grown as an invincible revolutionary army which is infinitely loyal to the leadership of the Party and moves as one under the order of the Supreme Commander. The people's army fully equipped with modern offensive and defensive means has been firmly prepared as a creditable shield with strong nuclear deterrent to defend the socialist homeland. The exploits of Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il which has brought the Korean nation, once a ruined nation subjugated by the imperialists in the early 20th century, on to the position of a dignified strongest power today 100 years after are the great patriotic exploits that should be highly praised and glorified generation after generation. 
 The high dignity and glory of the Party is the absolute prestige of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il who founded and led the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cause of the Party advancing under the banner of Songun is invincible forever.  The Songun idea and politics will always be the life and soul and eternal banner of victory of the Party, the article concludes.

Reception Given by German Ambassador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- German Ambassador to the DPRK Friedrich Ludwig Loehr gave a reception at the embassy Monday evening on the occasion of the national day of the Federal Republic of Germany.
 Present on invitation were Kung Sok Ung, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, officials concerned, foreign diplomatic envoys and representatives of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were staff members of the German embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

National Dishes, Pride of Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- Korean dishes have been famous in the world for their peculiar taste, odor, colors, diversity, scientific accuracy in cooking and medicinal effect.
 Korean ancestors had used grass, fruits, grass roots, meat, fishes, etc. as materials for food on the Korean peninsula from time immemorial. In the early Neolithic era, they cultivated grains including rice, bean, millet, sorghum and red-bean and bred domestic animals including pig. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this course, the main Korean national dishes including boiled rice and other grain food, subsidiary dishes including soup and drinks were created. 
 During Kojoson (ancient Korea) (early 30th century BC - 108 BC) they made taffy and sweet drink on the basis of the saccharification of enzyme and later, made soy, bean paste and kimchi on the principle of fermentation of microorganism.
 They made and used bean and green-bean sprouts and bean-curds in their dietary life.
 They found methods of cooking digestible food by putting pickled shrimps in sliced pork, pear in beef and celery in fishes including mackerel and methods of cooking poisonous food materials including puffer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Combination of food materials and components of dishes for meal meet the nutritive demand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The food materials of the boiled rice mixed with four other grains, sweet rice dish, fried rice and noodle are well mixed on a scientific basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, a set dinner properly consists of meat, vegetable, acid and alkaline dishes such as boiled rice, soup, kimchi and various subsidiary dishes.

National Book Exhibition Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 4 (KCNA) -- A national book exhibition opened with due ceremony at the Grand People's Study House Tuesday to celebrate the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea. 
 Displayed there are at least 39,000 books and magazines of more than 22,000 kinds out of those published in the DPRK and different countries up to this date since Korea's liberation. Among them are works of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il and books dealing with the history of revolutionary activities of the peerlessly great persons and the immortal exploits performed by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibition is divided into some rooms for publishing houses and distribution networks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Books showing the greatness and exploits of the party and the leader including "Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works",  "Kim Jong Il's Selected Works," "Great Personality of  Kim Jong Il," "Accomplishing Juche Revolutionary Cause" and "Korea, I Will Glorify Thee" and books explaining the Juche idea and the policies of the WPK, its embodiment, and socio-political books are on display in the rooms for publishing houses such as the Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House, the Science and Encyclopedia Press, the  Kum Song Youth Publishing House, the Literary and Art Publishing House, the Educational Book Publishing House, the Industrial Publishing House and the Foreign Languages Publishing House. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also displayed there are different kinds of books dealing with various domains, magazines and dictionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the rooms for the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and distribution networks are a variety of books including "Proud Path Covered by Chongryon" and magazines and books published in foreign countries praising the greatness of the three generals of Mt. Paektu and the immortal exploits performed by them including "Kim Il Sung, the Great Leader of the People in the 20th Century" and "Kim Jong Il, Leader of Korea" and those introducing the DPRK demonstrating the might of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jong Ha Chol, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK, addressed the opening ceremony.
